cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a meta-learning approach for learning causal structures and disentangling causal mechanisms. The paper discusses the use of continuous variables and end-to-end learning, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of encoders and representations, which are common in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of sparse expected gradients and a lower effective number of degrees of freedom, which are common in neural networks (cs.NE).
